    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add\u00a0the <strong>pork & beef\u00a0rag\u00f9 mince</strong>\u00a0to a bowl with the<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix thoroughly to combine</p><p>Divide the mixture into 10 <span class=\"text-danger\">[20]</span> and shape them into <strong>meatballs</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-meatball-tomato-and-courgette-orzo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> meatballs</strong> and cook for 3-4 min, turning occasionally, until browned all over</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>browned meatballs</strong> to a plate and set aside</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-meatball-tomato-and-courgette-orzo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the meatballs are browning, peel and finely\u00a0chop the <strong>brown\u00a0onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat and add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-meatball-tomato-and-courgette-orzo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is softening, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop the<strong> courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters, then into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr beef stock cube</strong> in 400ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [750ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-meatball-tomato-and-courgette-orzo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and <strong>orzo</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat\u00a0everything in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>beef stock</strong> with the <strong>tomato frito</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and a generous grind of<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-meatball-tomato-and-courgette-orzo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the orzo with the <strong>browned meatballs</strong> and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the orzo is tender and the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>meatball, tomato & courgette orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Keep an eye on the orzo and stir it\u00a0to stop it from sticking!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-meatball-tomato-and-courgette-orzo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-meatball-tomato-and-courgette-orzo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meatball, tomato & courgette orzo</strong>\u00a0in bowls topped with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>chopped basil</strong> and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
